# Always push changes

After finishing any code change in this project:

1. Commit the relevant files with a clear message (unless the user said not to commit).
2. Immediately push to the remote tracking branch (`git push -u origin HEAD` if needed).
3. Do not leave finished work only local — push is required by default for this repo.
4. Skip push only if the user explicitly says not to, or if there is nothing to commit.

Never force-push to `main`/`master` unless the user explicitly requests it.
